raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert I
raw_data.description: A professional possessing deep knowledge and experience in one or more specialized functional or domain areas. They offer guidance and insights regarding the strategic direction and the implementation of the latest industry-standard solutions. Their role includes delivering a broad perspective to senior client leadership or program/project managers to shape the goals of intricate projects. Although not serving in a managerial role, the Functional/Subject Matter Expert assists in formulating detailed ways to depict the current or future aspects of an organization's processes, systems, employees, and sub-units to ensure alignment with the main objectives and strategic path. Typically, this expert is a retired high-level military or civilian official and is acknowledged by the industry as a specialist in their particular field.
